title: Biden received a Pfizer-BioNTech booster.
content: The move comes only days after federal regulators moved to allow millions of Americans to get Pfizer booster shots.

title: ‘I was wrong’: Liz Cheney announces support for same-sex marriage, reversing a longstanding position.
content: Representative Liz Cheney came out against same-sex marriage in 2013. Her sister, who is gay, wrote online at the time that the decision put her “on the wrong side of history.”

title: Explaining the U.S. Debt Limit and Why It Became a Bargaining Tool
content: Political polarization turned a tool for fiscal responsibility into a recipe for economic calamity.

title: The Secret War Over Pentagon Aid in Fighting Wildfires
content: The military’s satellites excel at spotting new blazes, but for decades they have been mostly off limits to civilian firefighters.

title: No Veggies, No Buns, Few Forks: Schools Scramble to Feed Students Amid Shortages
content: Schools across the country are offering less healthy lunch options as they struggle with dwindling supplies, delayed shipments and fewer cafeteria workers.

title: How an Anti-Trump Plotter in 2016 Became His Champion Against Liz Cheney
content: Harriet Hageman, a Wyoming Republican, is the former president’s choice to take on his leading G.O.P. critic. But five years ago, she tried to overturn his victory in the party’s primary race.

title: Republicans Have Long Been Mad at General Milley. They Will Get Their Shot.
content: Gen. Mark Milley will appear in what could be the most significant televised congressional hearing involving senior military leaders in years.

title: India Walton Beat the Buffalo Mayor in a Primary. He Won’t Give Up.
content: India Walton, the democratic socialist who won the Democratic primary for Buffalo mayor, still faces a challenge from Mayor Byron Brown, who is running a write-in campaign against her.

title: Why Scores of Female Athletes Are Speaking Out on Abortion Rights
content: With a Supreme Court ruling in the balance, an Olympic medalist joined a group of more than 500 athletes supporting reproductive rights.

title: Pelosi Announces Vote on $1 Trillion Bipartisan Infrastructure Bill
content: Speaker Nancy Pelosi of California said that the House would take up the $1 trillion bill on Thursday, hours before government funding is scheduled to lapse.

title: America’s Need to Pay Its Bills Has Spawned a Political Game
content: Republicans and Democrats have long sparred over raising the debt ceiling. But this time, the odds are growing that the U.S. could default.

title: Freed From Guantánamo, but Still in Limbo 15 Years Later
content: Abu Bakker Qassim, a Uyghur from China, was dumped in Albania after the U.S. concluded he was not a terrorist, as Chinese authorities had maintained. The only country that wants him is China.

title: For Schumer and Pelosi, the Challenge of a Career With No Margin for Error
content: The top two Democrats in Congress face a daunting pile of legislative imperatives. With President Biden’s agenda hanging in the balance and few votes to spare, can they get it done?

title: Democrats’ Spending Fight Carries High Stakes for Their Candidates
content: Failure of moderates and progressives to reach a deal would fuel Republican attacks on their competence — with consequences as soon as November in Virginia, and in the midterms next year.

title: ‘Stop the Steal’ Movement Races Forward, Ignoring Arizona Humiliation
content: As a Republican review of 2020 votes in Arizona sputtered to a close, Donald Trump and his allies signaled that their attack on the election, and their drive to reshape future elections, were far from over.

title: U.S. Agrees to Release Huawei Executive in Case That Strained Ties With China
content: China reciprocated within hours, freeing two Canadians, a notable resolution in a relationship that has been spiraling downward.

title: Ocasio-Cortez apologizes for her ‘present’ vote on Iron Dome funding.
content: In a letter to constituents, the New York congresswoman suggested she had changed her “no” vote because she had been subjected to “hateful targeting” for opposing the aid.

title: Rebuking Biden, Iran’s Chief Diplomat Demands More Sanctions Relief
content: The foreign minister for Iran’s new hard-line government said it would demand a higher price for limiting its nuclear program than it did in the 2015 deal.

title: States Begin a Complex Booster Shot Rollout for Pfizer Recipients
content: Health officials were preparing on Friday to start giving booster shots to older and at-risk Americans, trying to make sense of new and broad eligibility guidelines.

title: How Democrats Could Shrink Their $3.5 Trillion Budget Bill
content: Here are three options to shrink down the Democrats’ climate change and social welfare bill as moderates demand less spending and smaller tax hikes to pay for it.

title: Biden Promised to Follow the Science. But Sometimes, He Gets Ahead of the Experts.
content: White House officials dismiss criticism that President Biden’s comments on booster shots amount to undue pressure on public health experts.

title: ‘Better to wait your turn in line,’ Biden says to those not yet eligible for Covid booster shots.
content: The authorization for boosters applies to groups of people in the United States fully vaccinated with the Pfizer vaccine, but about 45 percent of the country’s fully inoculated people received Moderna or Johnson & Johnson doses.

title: House Democrats say they plan action next week on the infrastructure bill and their social safety net plan.
content: An infrastructure vote had already been planned for Monday, and top Democrats said they also intended to take up their larger social policy and climate package.

title: Sherwood Boehlert, a G.O.P Moderate in the House, Dies at 84
content: A champion of environmentalism who chided climate-change skeptics, he was among the last of the relatively progressive Rockefeller Republicans.
